modules.description: Handles arithmetic and comparison operations on typed ordered fuzzy numbers, including addition, multiplication, and ordering. Works with custom data types representing fuzzy numbers with associated types and orderings. Used for implementing fuzzy logic computations in decision-making systems and uncertainty modeling.

Provides operations for adding, subtracting, multiplying, and dividing typed ordered fuzzy numbers (OFNs), along with type-checking and conversion between OFN families. Works with OFNs represented as structured tuples and family types defining their classification. Enables precise arithmetic on fuzzy numeric representations, such as converting between increasing and decreasing OFN types or evaluating membership values within specific ranges.
